    <item>
      <title>Brandy Alexander</title>
      <link>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/brandy-alexander/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2018 11:17:51 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/brandy-alexander/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;ul class=&#34;ingredients&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;2 oz Cognac or other brandy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;1 oz heavy cream&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;½ oz demerara syrup&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;fresh grated nutmeg&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;div class=&#34;instructions e-instructions&#34;&gt;
  Add brandy, cream, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/ingredients/simple-syrups/#variants&#34;&gt;demerara syrup&lt;/a&gt; to a cocktail shaker. Shake. Strain into coupe glass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Top with grated nutmeg.
&lt;/div&gt;


</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Sidecar</title>
      <link>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/sidecar/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 08 Jan 2018 11:17:50 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/sidecar/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;div class=&#34;recipe-intro p-summary&#34;&gt;The simple syrup isn’t traditional, but that’s how I learned it, and I like the touch of additional sweetness.&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;ul class=&#34;ingredients&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;2 oz Cognac&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;¾ oz orange liqueur&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;¾ oz lemon juice&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;¼ oz simple syrup&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;p-ingredient&#34;&gt;orange twist, discarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;instructions e-instructions&#34;&gt;
  Shake vigorously with ice. Strain into a coupe glass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Express the oils from an orange twist over the drink, then &lt;a href=&#34;https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/techniques/twist/#discarding&#34;&gt;discard the peel&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/div&gt;


</description>
